50|$|The <b>fiery-capped</b> <b>manakin</b> {{is found}} in the {{southern}} Amazon Basin of Brazil, southeast Peru, and northern Bolivia; also Venezuela. Itsnatural habitat is subtropical or tropical moist lowland forests.|$|E
50|$|The <b>fiery-capped</b> <b>manakin</b> (Machaeropterus pyrocephalus) is {{a species}} of bird in the Pipridae family, the manakins. It {{is one of three}} species in the genus Machaeropterus. It is named for its bright yellow head feathers.|$|E
50|$|Two small disjunct {{populations of}} the <b>fiery-capped</b> <b>manakin</b> occur; one in {{northeast}} Roraima state on the south-flowing Branco River; the other further northwest on the lower reaches of the Caribbean-flowing Orinoco River in east-central Venezuela, 500 km upstream.|$|E

